[
  {
    "text": "iPhone X's super retina display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=1"
  },
  {
    "text": "gives you more space to display content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "and create deeply immersive experiences. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "This video will help you get started ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=8"
  },
  {
    "text": "designing apps and games that look and feel great ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "across all iOS devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, let's review some key aspects ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the new display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPhone X 's display has a 3x image scale factor. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "When producing and delivering image assets, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=23"
  },
  {
    "text": "we recommend using PDFs because they're resolution-independent ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=26"
  },
  {
    "text": "and may significantly reduce the size of your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=29"
  },
  {
    "text": "When rasterized images are needed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "be sure to include both 2x and 3x resolutions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your app's asset catalog. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "To streamline your production process, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=40"
  },
  {
    "text": "we suggest using the templates included ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=43"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the Apple UI Design Resources. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=45"
  },
  {
    "text": "They're available to download on the Resources page ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=48"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the Apple Human Interface Guidelines.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=50"
  },
  {
    "text": "The iPhone X's display dimensions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "are 375 points wide by 812 points tall. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "On a 3x display, this equals 1125 by 2436 pixels. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "375 points is the same width as the 4.7 inch displays ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "of iPhone 6, iPhone 7 and iPhone 8. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "So there shouldn't be any difference ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=79"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the amount of information presented ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "along the narrower dimension of these devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "The 812 point height is 145 points taller ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "than a 4.7 inch display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=91"
  },
  {
    "text": "This additional height ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=93"
  },
  {
    "text": "provides about 20 percent more space for content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "Of course, the most notable feature ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=98"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the super retina display is its shape. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "The display follows the design of the product ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "around all four rounded corners for a symmetrical look. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "Updating your app to work on the new display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=110"
  },
  {
    "text": "involves extending visual elements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "to fill the display's view port, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "while also keeping controls and critical information ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=118"
  },
  {
    "text": "from getting clipped in the corners ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "or covered by the sensor housing. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "people access the app switcher and the Home screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "by swiping up anywhere ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=131"
  },
  {
    "text": "along the bottom edge of the display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=133"
  },
  {
    "text": "An indicator at the bottom of the screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "offers a hint about this interaction. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "This indicator is displayed over your app's interface. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "You'll need to account for this when designing your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app uses UIKit controls and auto-layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "designing and developing for iPhone X ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=152"
  },
  {
    "text": "and our other devices should be straightforward. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "Standard UIKit elements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as navigation bars, tables, and collection views, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=159"
  },
  {
    "text": "automatically adjust when viewed on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "Navigation bars, tab bars, and toolbars ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=168"
  },
  {
    "text": "are positioned and scaled appropriately ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=171"
  },
  {
    "text": "on all iOS devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=173"
  },
  {
    "text": "The navigation bar's background material ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "is extended to the display's top edge, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the background material of the tab bar and toolbar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "is extended to the bottom, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "while the elements they contain ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=187"
  },
  {
    "text": "are positioned to prevent underlapping ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "or clipping by other elements. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=191"
  },
  {
    "text": "In landscape orientation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=195"
  },
  {
    "text": "table views will span the full width of the display, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "while the table cell's content view is inset. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app uses auto-layout, views can automatically adapt ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=204"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the iPhone X's larger display size. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "For iOS 11, a new layout guide was added to auto-layout ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=212"
  },
  {
    "text": "called a Safe Area layout guide. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=216"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Safe Area layout guide ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=219"
  },
  {
    "text": "helps avoid underlapping system UI elements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=220"
  },
  {
    "text": "when positioning content and controls. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPhone 8, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Safe Area is the same size as the viewport ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=228"
  },
  {
    "text": "if no bars are visible. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=231"
  },
  {
    "text": "If a status bar is visible, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "the safe area's top edge is lowered ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "to account for the status bar's height. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Safe Area is further inset ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "to accommodate a navigation bar and toolbar or tab bar. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=244"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=249"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Safe Area layout guide provides an additional benefit. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=251"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's inset from the top and bottom of the screen edges ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "in portrait orientation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "even when no bars are visible on screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=260"
  },
  {
    "text": "This helps you to prevent interface elements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "fromÂ getting clipped or covered ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=266"
  },
  {
    "text": "by positioning them away from the sensor housing, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=268"
  },
  {
    "text": "the display's rounded corners, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the Home indicator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "In landscape orientation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Safe Area is inset from the sides of the screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=277"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the Home indicator for the same reason. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "So, for example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "the width of the content view in these table row cells ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "is constrained by the Safe Area ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "to keep them from underlapping the sensor housing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "or getting clipped ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "by the display's rounded corners. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "And the table's top edge has been inset ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=299"
  },
  {
    "text": "to avoid underlapping the navigation bar.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPhone 8, where occlusion and clipping is not an issue, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Safe Area width matches the display's width ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=309"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the table is allowed to run edge-to-edge. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=312"
  },
  {
    "text": "You'll notice that text and controls ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=315"
  },
  {
    "text": "are actually inset from the safe area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=317"
  },
  {
    "text": "This inset is achieved using another layout guide ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "called a layout margin. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=323"
  },
  {
    "text": "Layout margins provide ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "consistent content margins across apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=326"
  },
  {
    "text": "and help you to align content to other controls ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "like navigation bar buttons. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=332"
  },
  {
    "text": "Even if you're not using auto-layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "UIView provides the Safe Area insets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "and layout margin values as properties. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=341"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, one final note about auto-layout. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=344"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPhone 6, 7, 8, and X ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=348"
  },
  {
    "text": "all belong in the compact width size class. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=351"
  },
  {
    "text": "This essentially means that your app's layout ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=355"
  },
  {
    "text": "should be consistent on all these devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app has custom controls ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "or non-standard layouts, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may need to make slight alterations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=366"
  },
  {
    "text": "to your app's interface to work well on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are two aspects to this. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, your app or game ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=375"
  },
  {
    "text": "should always fill the display that it runs on. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=377"
  },
  {
    "text": "Placing black bars at the top or bottom of the screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=380"
  },
  {
    "text": "makes your app feel small, cramped, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=384"
  },
  {
    "text": "and inconsistent with other apps on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=386"
  },
  {
    "text": "When designing background graphics, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "or rendering background scenes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=392"
  },
  {
    "text": "keep in mind that iPhone X's display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=394"
  },
  {
    "text": "has a different aspect ratio than a 4.7 inch display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=396"
  },
  {
    "text": "Background graphics designed for iPhone 8's 16:9 aspect ratio ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=401"
  },
  {
    "text": "will be cropped along the left and right edges on iPhone X ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=406"
  },
  {
    "text": "if they're scaled to fill, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=411"
  },
  {
    "text": "or letter-boxed if scaled to fit. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=413"
  },
  {
    "text": "Similarly, background graphics designed for iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=417"
  },
  {
    "text": "will either be cropped ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=421"
  },
  {
    "text": "along the top and bottom edges on iPhone 8 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=422"
  },
  {
    "text": "or pillar-boxed. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's best compose images ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=427"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that critical visual information remains visible ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=429"
  },
  {
    "text": "regardless of the display's aspect ratio. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "The second part of updating your layout involves insetting, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=436"
  },
  {
    "text": "or repositioning interactive elements and key information. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=440"
  },
  {
    "text": "Any element that's positioned ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "too close to the viewport's edges or corners ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=447"
  },
  {
    "text": "may get clipped by the display's rounded corners ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=450"
  },
  {
    "text": "or covered by the sensor housing. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=453"
  },
  {
    "text": "So be sure to inset controls ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=456"
  },
  {
    "text": "and other elements to avoid this.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=458"
  },
  {
    "text": "Again, Safe Area layout guides and layout margins ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=461"
  },
  {
    "text": "should be used for determining proper inset values. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=464"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's also worth noting ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "that controls placed along a device's edge ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=470"
  },
  {
    "text": "could be more difficult to reach ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=473"
  },
  {
    "text": "depending on how the device is held. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=475"
  },
  {
    "text": "Insetting controls can make interacting with them faster ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=477"
  },
  {
    "text": "and more comfortable.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=480"
  },
  {
    "text": "Visual elements that appear tucked into corners ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=483"
  },
  {
    "text": "or under screen edges may need to be revised ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "since insetting them probably won't look right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "In some cases, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "a different visual treatment may be necessary.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=494"
  },
  {
    "text": "Please also note that status bars are taller ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=499"
  },
  {
    "text": "on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=502"
  },
  {
    "text": "Content views that have been inset ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "by a fixed point value ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=505"
  },
  {
    "text": "will have their top edges covered by the status bar. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=507"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPhone X, the status bar no longer changes height ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=511"
  },
  {
    "text": "when background tasks, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "like a phone call or location tracking, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=516"
  },
  {
    "text": "are running. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=519"
  },
  {
    "text": "This helps create a more consistent user experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=520"
  },
  {
    "text": "regardless of the status bar style.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "On iPhone X, the status bar occupies an area of the screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=529"
  },
  {
    "text": "that your app probably won't fully utilize. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=534"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you have hidden the status bar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=537"
  },
  {
    "text": "to claim more space for your app's interface, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=539"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may want to reconsider if that's still necessary. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=542"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, one quick note about landscape orientation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=546"
  },
  {
    "text": "Most apps look and function best ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=550"
  },
  {
    "text": "when controls and visual information are centered. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=552"
  },
  {
    "text": "Asymmetrical layouts that shift around ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=556"
  },
  {
    "text": "based on how the device is rotated ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=559"
  },
  {
    "text": "will lead to an inconsistent user experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=561"
  },
  {
    "text": "and can undermine people's ability ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=564"
  },
  {
    "text": "to build muscle memory.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=566"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, a few key considerations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=569"
  },
  {
    "text": "related to the indicator ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=572"
  },
  {
    "text": "that let's people know they can swipe up ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=573"
  },
  {
    "text": "to access the app switcher and Home Screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=575"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because this interaction is core to the experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=579"
  },
  {
    "text": "of using an iOS device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=582"
  },
  {
    "text": "the indicator should always be clearly visible. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=584"
  },
  {
    "text": "To help accomplish this, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=587"
  },
  {
    "text": "iOS dynamically adjusts the indicator's appearance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=589"
  },
  {
    "text": "to maintain sufficient contrast relative to the background. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=592"
  },
  {
    "text": "The indicator appears dark against lighter backgrounds, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=597"
  },
  {
    "text": "and light against darker backgrounds. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=600"
  },
  {
    "text": "When designing your app's interface ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=603"
  },
  {
    "text": "to work well with the Home indicator, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=605"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's best to avoid placing interface elements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=607"
  },
  {
    "text": "in close proximity to the indicator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=610"
  },
  {
    "text": "Simply leave some negative space around the indicator ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=614"
  },
  {
    "text": "by placing all non-scrollable content within the safe area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=617"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's also not desirable ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=622"
  },
  {
    "text": "to draw special attention to the indicator ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=623"
  },
  {
    "text": "through visual adornments ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as brackets, bezels, or other means.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=628"
  },
  {
    "text": "As mentioned earlier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=633"
  },
  {
    "text": "people will access the app switcher and Home screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=634"
  },
  {
    "text": "by swiping upward ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=637"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the bottom edge of the display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=639"
  },
  {
    "text": "In most cases, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=641"
  },
  {
    "text": "swipe gestures tend to occur in the center of the display, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=642"
  },
  {
    "text": "so this interaction is unlikely to conflict ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=646"
  },
  {
    "text": "with interactions in your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=649"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, if your app or game encourages people ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=652"
  },
  {
    "text": "to swipe along the very bottom of the display, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=655"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may want to turn on edge protection ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=658"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the bottom edge of the display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=661"
  },
  {
    "text": "This will give the indicator a more subtle appearance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=664"
  },
  {
    "text": "and change it's behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=667"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that two swipes are required to exit your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=668"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first swipe, or drag, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=672"
  },
  {
    "text": "lifts the indicator and enables the control. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=674"
  },
  {
    "text": "While swiping a second time ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=678"
  },
  {
    "text": "allows people to exit your app or game. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=680"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because edge protection leads to an inconsistent user experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=683"
  },
  {
    "text": "it should be used only when it's absolutely necessary. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=688"
  },
  {
    "text": "Unlike swipes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=692"
  },
  {
    "text": "tapping the bottom edge of the display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=693"
  },
  {
    "text": "will only affect your app or game. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=695"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, tapping a table row cell ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "has the same result ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=701"
  },
  {
    "text": "whether or not it's behind the indicator.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=702"
  },
  {
    "text": "Vertically scrollable views, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=706"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as tables or collection views, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=708"
  },
  {
    "text": "should extend all the way to the bottom of the display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=710"
  },
  {
    "text": "rather than being constrained by the Safe Area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=713"
  },
  {
    "text": "Lastly, you can enable an auto-hide behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=717"
  },
  {
    "text": "when presenting full screen visual content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=720"
  },
  {
    "text": "Auto-hide causes the indicator to fade out ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=725"
  },
  {
    "text": "if the display hasn't been touched for a few seconds ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=727"
  },
  {
    "text": "and fade back in when the display is touched. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=730"
  },
  {
    "text": "Use auto-hide sparingly and only for passive experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=734"
  },
  {
    "text": "where people are unlikely to touch the display frequently. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=738"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, for more iPhone X design guidance, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=743"
  },
  {
    "text": "please visit the Apple Human Interface Guidelines ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=746"
  },
  {
    "text": "at developer.apple.com/design. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=749"
  },
  {
    "text": "And while you're there, download the latest version ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=753"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the iOS Apple UI Design Resources. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=755"
  },
  {
    "text": "We've updated the Sketch and Photoshop templates ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=758"
  },
  {
    "text": "for iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=761"
  },
  {
    "text": "and there will be more updates\ncoming soon.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-801/?time=763"
  }
]